The next day, strain out zest from oil and drizzle slowly into passed tomatoes as you constantly stir.  When all the oil is incorporated, season with salt and pepper.  Allow the sauce to sit once more for a bit to allow the flavors to come together.
To serve: Give the sauce a good stir as it will have surely separated and toss with hot thin pasta and a sprinkle of grated aged pecorino (sheep''s milk cheese) or parmesan.', 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/4CDSCY2Y/pasta-with-raw-tomato-lemon-infused-olive-oil', 'Foodista.com – The Cooking Encyclopedia Everyone Can Edit', 'extra virgin olive oil
