Heat glaze ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat until runny, about 5 minutes.
Remove ham from oven, and uncover. Score ham all over in a diamond pattern. Brush 1/2 of the glaze over ham.
Increase temperature to 425 degrees. Bake ham, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Brush with remaining glaze, and bake until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes more. Let rest for 15 to 30 minutes before slicing.', 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TV3JLDLH/ham-with-orange-rosemary-marmalade-glaze', 'Foodista.com – The Cooking Encyclopedia Everyone Can Edit', 'ham
